This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it focuses on accelerating the test-time computation of deep convolutional neural networks for image classification tasks. It also involves the use of ImageNet, a large-scale image dataset commonly used in computer vision research. 

The paper also involves optimization techniques, which suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. 

Additionally, the paper involves the use of nonlinear units in CNNs, which could place it in the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. 

The use of low-rank constraints to reduce filter complexity could also place the paper in the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. 

Finally, the paper involves the evaluation of the model's accuracy, which could place it in the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
